WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.675 --> 00:00:04.365
Welcome to the animated series on high volume hemo

2
00:00:04.765 --> 00:00:07.645
filtration hosted by life nephrology campus.

3
00:00:08.465 --> 00:00:09.565
In the first episode,

4
00:00:09.865 --> 00:00:12.645
we will review the recently published convinced trial.

5
00:00:12.835 --> 00:00:15.685
Currently one of the biggest randomized controlled outcome

6
00:00:15.695 --> 00:00:16.965
trial in dialysis.

7
00:00:18.475 --> 00:00:21.205
High blood pressure, diabetes, infections,

8
00:00:21.425 --> 00:00:24.045
and inherited diseases are the leading causes

9
00:00:24.045 --> 00:00:26.085
that contribute to chronic kidney disease.

10
00:00:26.395 --> 00:00:27.965
Approximately 10%

11
00:00:27.965 --> 00:00:30.925
of the general population suffer from kidney damage,

12
00:00:31.185 --> 00:00:32.525
and a substantial portion

13
00:00:32.545 --> 00:00:35.765
of these patients progress into end stage kidney disease.

14
00:00:36.155 --> 00:00:39.165
Prompting the initiation of kidney replacement therapy.

15
00:00:40.105 --> 00:00:44.965
In fact, one in 6,800 Europeans start kidney replacement

16
00:00:44.965 --> 00:00:46.085
therapy every year.

17
00:00:47.025 --> 00:00:50.525
In 2016, the overall five year survival rate

18
00:00:50.525 --> 00:00:54.645
of patients on kidney replacement therapy was as low as 52%.

19
00:00:56.085 --> 00:00:58.165
Hemodialysis is the most common form

20
00:00:58.165 --> 00:01:01.685
of kidney replacement therapy, followed by transplantation

21
00:01:01.985 --> 00:01:03.565
and peritoneal dialysis.

22
00:01:04.275 --> 00:01:06.805
Over the past four decades, the landscape

23
00:01:06.805 --> 00:01:09.125
of dialysis technologies accessible

24
00:01:09.125 --> 00:01:11.965
to clinicians has undergone a significant improvement.

25
00:01:13.425 --> 00:01:15.485
It has transitioned from acetate

26
00:01:15.665 --> 00:01:17.765
to bicarbonate based solutions.

27
00:01:18.565 --> 00:01:22.645
Improved dialyzer membrane biocompatibility shifted from low

28
00:01:22.715 --> 00:01:26.685
flux to high flux dialyzer transition from contaminated

29
00:01:26.705 --> 00:01:28.645
to ultrapure dialysis fluid,

30
00:01:28.945 --> 00:01:32.165
and finally, from diffusive to connective modalities Like

31
00:01:32.795 --> 00:01:37.125
diafiltration, hemofiltration combines

32
00:01:37.135 --> 00:01:39.485
convective and diffusive methods together

33
00:01:39.715 --> 00:01:41.365
with high flux dialyzer.

34
00:01:43.565 --> 00:01:46.205
A growing body of evidence indicates that treatment

35
00:01:46.205 --> 00:01:50.045
with hemofiltration is associated with reduced all cause

36
00:01:50.105 --> 00:01:51.845
and cardiovascular mortality.

37
00:01:52.705 --> 00:01:55.965
In 2023, the findings from the convinced trial,

38
00:01:56.095 --> 00:01:59.965
which examined whether high volume hemo filtration provides

39
00:02:00.165 --> 00:02:01.565
survival benefits compared

40
00:02:01.565 --> 00:02:04.525
to conventional high flux hemodialysis were published.

41
00:02:05.195 --> 00:02:08.925
High volume hemo filtration refers to treatment sessions,

42
00:02:08.925 --> 00:02:10.605
which achieve target volumes

43
00:02:10.745 --> 00:02:12.805
of more than 23 liters per session.

44
00:02:13.185 --> 00:02:17.525
In post dilution mode enroll patients were likely candidates

45
00:02:17.665 --> 00:02:19.845
for the high volume hemo filtration.

46
00:02:20.625 --> 00:02:24.685
In the largest hemo filtration trial involving patients in

47
00:02:24.685 --> 00:02:28.965
eight European countries, investigators highlighted the 23%

48
00:02:29.525 --> 00:02:31.885
decrease in all cause mortality within the

49
00:02:32.035 --> 00:02:33.325
hemo filtration group.

50
00:02:34.225 --> 00:02:35.725
Beyond survival benefits,

51
00:02:35.985 --> 00:02:39.085
the convinced study demonstrated the successful achievement

52
00:02:39.185 --> 00:02:41.125
of high convective volume in the clinic,

53
00:02:41.515 --> 00:02:44.605
achieving the targeted 23 liters session in

54
00:02:44.605 --> 00:02:46.205
92% of treatments.

55
00:02:47.075 --> 00:02:50.645
Furthermore, the proven safety, high patient tolerance,

56
00:02:50.705 --> 00:02:54.405
and comparable patient adherence rates across both dialysis

57
00:02:54.405 --> 00:02:56.605
modalities supports the integration

58
00:02:56.745 --> 00:03:00.165
of hemo filtration into standard clinical practice.

59
00:03:01.145 --> 00:03:04.205
In the next episode, we'll explain what makes the difference

60
00:03:04.205 --> 00:03:07.925
between a hemodialysis and hemofiltration treatment.

